  "directional_assessment": {
    "scene_level_modal": "NOT directionally stable -- modal scene ensemble is duo (25.9%) in crystal_shard, quad_plus (65.8%) in streams_of_silver, quad_plus (46.0%) in halflings_gem. Streams_of_silver's quad_plus dominance is a scene-segmentation artifact (median 952w/scene). Use beat-level signal instead.",
    "beat_level_modal": "Directionally stable: solo is the single modal beat-ensemble in all 3 books (37.9% / 31.9% / 34.6%). Solo + duo together comprise 60-66% of beats in every book.",
    "top_pair_stability": "4 pairs appear in all three books' top-10 (Bruenor + Drizzt, Bruenor + Wulfgar, Drizzt + Regis, Drizzt + Wulfgar). The Companions-of-the-Hall core (Drizzt, Bruenor, Wulfgar, Regis, Catti-brie) dominates books 2 and 3; book 1 top-10 includes Akar Kessell pairings (Drizzt + Akar Kessell appears in book 1 top-10 only).",
    "headline": "Beat-level ensemble shape is directionally stable across the trilogy: the modal beat is solo-character (~34%), with duo close behind (~22-34%), and trio+ rare (~7-15%). At the chapter granularity, however, chapters mostly mix multiple ensemble sizes -- most chapters have at least one quad+ scene as the planner-relevant 'big-cast moment'."
  },
  "harness_target": {
    "planner_section": "src/agents/planning-plotter/chapter-outline-system.md and src/agents/planning-beats/beat-expansion-system.md",
    "recommended_prior": "Beat-level (beat-expansion-system.md): biased toward solo and duo beats -- modal beat should have 1 character on-page, secondary mode 2. Trio+ beats should be ~10-15% of any chapter, reserved for council/confrontation moments. Chapter-level (chapter-outline-system.md): each chapter typically contains a mix of solo + duo beats with >=1 trio+ scene; pure-solo chapters (no duo or larger) are rare (<10% of corpus). The charactersPresent field at the chapter level should NOT be the on-page ensemble for every beat -- it's a 'character pool' from which beats draw subsets.",
    "ship_status": "Candidate ship -- directional signal is clean at beat granularity. Scene-level signal is contaminated by streams_of_silver scene-segmentation differences and should not be used as a planner prior."
  }
